HOUSE RESOLUTION NO. 142
BY REPRESENTATIVE MARCELLE
COMMENDATIONS: Commends Etta Jane Harris on the occasion of her retirement as
deputy undersecretary of the Department of Children and Family Services
1 A RESOLUTION
2 To commend Etta Jane Harris for her contributions to the state of Louisiana on the occasion
3 of her retirement as deputy undersecretary of the Department of Children and Family
4 Services.
5 WHEREAS, it is appropriate to honor Etta Jane Harris for her service as deputy
6 undersecretary of the Department of Children and Family Services and to commend her on
7 the occasion of her retirement; and
8 WHEREAS, Etta Jane Harris was born on April 10, 1961, and is one of three
9 children born to James and Marie Harris; and
10 WHEREAS, Ms. Harris began her state employment journey at the age of nineteen,
11 and she has served the state with dedication and advocated for the well-being of its citizens;
12 and
13 WHEREAS, Ms. Harris has served with distinction for more than forty-four years;
14 her advocacy efforts have been focused on single-family housing, access to public services,
15 Louisiana children served by the division of child welfare, disabled individuals, and the
16 hungry and needy; and
17 WHEREAS, Ms. Harris received a bachelor of science degree in business
18 management and a master's degree in public administration with a concentration in budget
19 and finance from Southern University; and
20 WHEREAS, Ms. Harris served as a state budget manager for the commissioner of
21 administration under numerous governors and worked to support education, juvenile justice,
